  <p>
    <strong><em>Use of Medications</em></strong>
  </p>
  <p class="vspace">
    Controlled Substances: Contract employees are not permitted to work while using a medication that contains a controlled substance, unless (1) the employee’s use is authorized by and consistent with a valid prescription from a licensed medical provider, and (2) the use of the medication will not impair the employee’s ability to perform his or her job duties safely and effectively.
  </p>
  <p class="vspace">
    All Medications: Contract employees using medications are responsible to determine whether the medication could impair their ability to meet the Company’s requirements for safety, performance, and conduct. Employees are encourages to consult their physician or other appropriate medical provider for answers to questions about this.
  </p>
  <p class="vspace text-right">
    Revised: August 20, 2015
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong><em>Employment</em></strong>
  </p>
  <p class="vspace">
    If a contracted employee under consideration for regular hire tests positive, the contracted employee will no longer be considered for regular hire. In addition, the temporary agency will be notified of the test results and the contracted employee will no longer be allowed to work at Steelcase as a contracted employee.
  </p>
  <p class="vspace">
    Depending on employment opportunities in effect at the time, the candidate may re-apply after one year and be considered for employment if positions are available and the candidate meets Steelcase requirements.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong><em>Return from Leave</em></strong>
  </p>
  <p class="vspace">
    Contracted employees will be tested for drugs upon return from any leave of 30 days or more. Leaves are to include but are not limited to voluntary or involuntary layoff, personal or military. In the event of a confirmed positive test, the contracted employee will be discharged from the company.
  </p>
  <p class="vspace">
    Depending on employment opportunities in effect at the time, the former contracted employee may re-apply after one year and be considered for employment if positions are available and the individual meets Steelcase requirements.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>
      <em>Initial Visit to Medical Facility/ Involvement in Incident</em>
    </strong>
  </p>
  <p class="vspace">
    Contracted employees will be tested for alcohol and drugs prior to employment or upon involvement in an incident at a company provided medical facility. Contracted employees that bypass a safety device or when there is a safety violation with disabling injury imminent will be tested for alcohol and drugs.
  </p>
  <p class="vspace">
    City Fleet Drivers are subject to this policy if involved in an accident on company property. If involved in an accident while on the road, drivers are subject to substance abuse testing as required by Department of Transportation (DOT) regulations.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong><em>Possession and/or Under the Influence</em></strong>
  </p>
  <p>
    If a contracted employee is suspected of being under the influence of and /or in possession of a controlled substance or alcohol during working hours and/or while on company property:
  </p>
  <ol class="vspace">
